# AC-5 equivalents — ver equivalents-security-core.md
#
# RE-KEYED to STABLE-ID format: operator_name|start_row:start_col-end_row:end_col|occurrence
# (see stable_id() in mutkill_approval_grants.py). Stable-ids are re-init-proof:
# cosmic-ray regenerates random job_ids on every init, but the source-AST-derived
# stable-id is preserved byte-for-byte. The legacy 32-hex job_ids are gone.
#
# This file lists the 119 PROVEN-EQUIVALENT survivors. The 120th baseline survivor,
# match_command_set_grant's keyword-only `*` marker
# (core/ReplaceBinaryOperator_Mul_Div|1620:4-5|1), is RECLASSIFIED to KILLABLE and
# is killed by TestMatchCommandSetGrantMutants in test_approval_grants_mutants.py
# (asserts db_path is KEYWORD_ONLY). It is therefore NOT skipped here.
#
# Note also REMOVED vs the legacy file: the create_command_set_grant `*` kw-only
# marker at line 1546 (legacy ReplaceBinaryOperator_Mul_Div b428c87...) is no longer
# a survivor in the current session (that mutant now DIES), so it has no entry.

